{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Create a Cross-Departmental Strategy to end \"Zero-Consequence\" Culture for Crime",
        "additional_details": "We are concerned that UK communities may face a systemic collapse of order due to what we see as a \"zero-consequence\" culture. We think that policing \"low-value\" theft has become optional, effectively decriminalizing some crime and eroding public trust. Shifting any accountability to schools via collective bans is a failed strategy that ignores individual responsibility. Furthermore, we feel that current frameworks penalize integrity, leaving staff vulnerable to dismissal for upholding the law. We must restore the rule of law, protect moral action, and realign educational values.",
        "background": "The government should consider:  \r\nMandated police attendance for all retail crime, even \"low-value\" theft\r\nMore legal protection for staff from dismissal when upholding the law\r\nUpdated curriculum to teach more accountability\r\nMore direct consequences for offenders to replace collective school bans",
